This paper is about natural language processing and specifically about coreference resolution, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also describes a baseline system for mention detection and coreference resolution, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI, cs.LG). The use of multiple annotations and automatic adjudication suggests a focus on improving accuracy and efficiency, which could also fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
